strong>:</p>\n<p>Normally this problem is because there are multiple jQuery loaded to your WordPress. </p>\n<p>You can view the HTML source code of your webpage, and check how many jQuery are loaded in your website.</p>\n<p>In Google Chrome, you can view the HTML source code with menu View -> Developer -> View Source, then search text "jquery" in the source code.</p>\n<p>There should be only one jQuery in the webpage, which is added by the WordPress system.  </p>\n<p>Some plugins add their own jQuery to the website, and this is not correct. </p>\n<p>A plugin should always reply on the system installed jQuery, and the js files added from a plugin will be added after the system jQuery.</p>\n<p>A jQuery will destroy all other jQuery functions that are added before it. So if a plugin adds its own jQuery, it may destroy other jQuery functions. </p>\n<p><strong>To fix the issue:</strong></p>\n<p>You can try to disable all other plugins, and see whether the WonderPlugin works. If it works, you can then enable the plugins one by one, and find the plugin that causes the problem.</p>\n<p>If the WonderPlugin is still not working after you have disabled all other plugins, then the extra jQuery may have been added manually to the theme, you need to find the code and remove it.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:86:"http://www.wonderplugin.com/wordpress-slider/multiple-jquery-loaded-in-wordpress/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:45:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17